Authorities in India and Bangladesh are on high alert as Cyclone Sidr, with winds up to 240 km/h, threatens the region.
Evacuations are underway to protect hundreds of thousands of people from the destructive storm.
The cyclone hit the coast near the India-Bangladesh border, causing widespread devastation.
The United States and Germany have pledged aid to assist with relief efforts.
The storm has left a trail of destruction, with over 160 reported deaths and thousands displaced.
Emergency supplies are being distributed to those in need as the recovery process begins.
